      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I'd be happy to help clarify the interest calculation process for you. Each month, interest is typically calculated as a percentage of the outstanding principal balance, and this percentage remains the same for the entire term of the loan. This means the interest accrues daily and is added to the principal at the beginning of the month, dividing the monthly payment into two components: interest and principal. The difference between your monthly payment and the interest-plus-principal total is actually being allocated towards the principal, which is why you're making progress even if the principal balance doesn't seem to be decreasing much.",
